        "subject": "LU-12597 contrib: move comma_list rules for checkpatch",
        "message": "LU-12597 contrib: move comma_list rules for checkpatch\n\n\"checkpatch.pl\" uses \"userspace_spelling.txt\" for files in\nlustre/utils/, lustre/tests/, lnet/utils/, libcfs/libcfs/util/. For\nall other files, \"spelling.txt\" is used. Therefore,\n\"comma_list.*osts_nodes\" is currently not checked for lustre/tests/.\n\nThis patch fixes this, so the bash rules are applied correctly to\nlustre/tests/ instead of kernel files.\n\nFixes: a2d7e81c01 (\"LU-12597 tests: return comma-separated mdts_nodes()\")\nTest-Parameters: trivial\nSigned-off-by: Marc Vef <mvef@whamcloud.com>\nChange-Id: I94d5309342b96058778b31e3cac2c2f48727f815\nReviewed-on: https://review.whamcloud.com/c/fs/lustre-release/+/60817\nTested-by: Maloo <maloo@whamcloud.com>\nReviewed-by: Arshad Hussain <arshad.hussain@aeoncomputing.com>\nReviewed-by: Andreas Dilger <adilger@whamcloud.com>\nTested-by: jenkins <devops@whamcloud.com>\nReviewed-by: Oleg Drokin <green@whamcloud.com>\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
